════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2ead4); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:400; font-variation-settings:'opsz' 32; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">Affordable, well-connected and in demand: southern Brisbane's accessible suburb.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Coopers Plains occupies a practical and genuinely well-positioned place in Brisbane's southern property market. The Beenleigh/Gold Coast train line, with Coopers Plains station on the route, delivers direct CBD access that buyers and tenants consistently value. Combine that with an affordable price point relative to Robertson, Sunnybank Hills and Moorooka, and you have a suburb that absorbs spill-over demand from its more expensive neighbours on a regular basis.
    </p>
