    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:400; font-variation-settings:'opsz' 32; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:2.5rem;">Common questions about Coopers Plains.</h2>
    <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column;">

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What drives property values in Coopers Plains?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Coopers Plains values are driven by block size, proximity to the train station, property condition, and rental yield potential. The suburb's affordable price point means first-home buyers and investors are both active, and a well-maintained property with good rental history or clear owner-occupier appeal will attract genuine competition. The Beenleigh/Gold Coast rail line gives direct CBD access, and proximity to employment corridors at Moorooka and along the South East Freeway corridor supports values for tenants and owner-occupiers alike.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell a home in Coopers Plains?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Well-priced Coopers Plains properties typically sell within 22 to 38 days. The suburb's affordability and rail access create consistent demand from both investors and first-home buyers. Well-presented properties at accurate price points attract faster campaigns. The investor segment is active and can add competitive depth, particularly for properties with strong rental configurations.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the lifestyle like in Coopers Plains?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Coopers Plains is an established, well-connected southern Brisbane suburb that offers genuine affordability without sacrificing access. The Beenleigh/Gold Coast line at Coopers Plains station delivers direct CBD access, and the suburb sits within reach of employment at the Moorooka industrial and commercial precinct, the Princess Alexandra Hospital and Mater Hospital precinct, and Griffith University South Bank campus. It appeals to families who want southern Brisbane access at an affordable price point, and to investors drawn by consistent rental demand.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          Is Coopers Plains a good suburb to sell in right now?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Coopers Plains maintains consistent demand from a genuinely diverse buyer pool: investors, first-home buyers, and families priced out of Robertson, Sunnybank Hills and Moorooka. The suburb's affordability relative to its neighbours means it absorbs spill-over demand from higher-priced adjacent suburbs, and the rail connection provides a transport credential that supports values across market cycles. Well-presented homes at accurate price points attract competition from buyers who have been active across the southern corridor.</p>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

